title: Presidential Nominations Sent to the Senate | whitehouse.gov
content:
The White House
Office of the Press Secretary


For Immediate Release
April 14, 2016

 



Presidential Nominations Sent to the Senate





	NOMINATIONS SENT TO THE SENATE:

	Beth M. Andrus, of Washington, to be United States District Judge for the Western District of Washington, vice Robert S. Lasnik, retired.

	J. Michael Diaz, of Washington, to be United States District Judge for the Western District of Washington, vice James L. Robart, retiring.

	Kathleen M. O'Sullivan, of Washington, to be United States District Judge for the Western District of Washington, vice Marsha J. Pechman, retired.
